This paper deals with the problem of s-t reliability estimation in uncertain graphs, which is a fundamental problem in the field of database research. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various sampling and indexing based efficient algorithms, which are related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The problem of s-t reliability estimation involves graph traversal and path finding, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic graphs in emerging applications, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of experimental results, which is related to cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
